Key Match Events: Vincent Aboubakar scored an 8th-minute penalty for Cameroon.
Martin Hongla scored in the 39th minute for Cameroon.
Bryan Mbeumo scored in the 43rd minute for Cameroon.
Christian Bassogog scored in the 55th minute for Cameroon.
Michael Olunga scored in the 41st minute for Kenya.
David Nondi received a yellow card in the 30th minute for Kenya.
Pre-Game Insights: Both teams are without defeat after their opening two qualifiers.
Victory for either side would move them within touching distance of a place in Morocco.
Cameroon failed to make their dominance count against Zimbabwe on September 10, resulting in a goalless draw.
Cameroon is unbeaten in four matches across World Cup and AFCON qualifying duties since their continental exit at the hands of Nigeria.
Kenya narrowly edged Namibia 2-1 in their second qualifying outing.
Kenya is unbeaten in eight of nine involvements across all competitions in 2024.
Kenya has recorded five clean sheets since the turn of the year.
Kenya is aiming to feature at the AFCON for the first time since 2019.
